Issues found: 2
  - [FIXED] CI gate infinite loop for tasks with closed PRs (EMI-392 had 60 invocations)
    Root cause: `getPrCheckStatus(prNumber)` calls `gh pr checks` which returns "no commit
    found on the pull request" for closed PRs. The CI gate treated this as a transient error
    and kept retrying every 30 seconds indefinitely. EMI-392 was stuck in this loop with PR
    #141 closed (0 additions, 0 deletions — the PR had no commits at all).
    Fix: Added early exit in `runCiGateAndMerge()` (ci-merge.ts): if `task.prState === "closed"`,
    fail the task immediately with reason "pr_closed_not_merged". The fix runs on the next
    Inngest step callback — deployed instance will resolve EMI-392 in the next 30s poll cycle.
    Commit: see deploy commit.

  - [FIXED] TypeScript error TS2339 in reconcile-stuck-tasks.ts
    Root cause: `deps.activeHandles` referenced in the detect-stuck-tasks step but `SchedulerDeps`
    type has no `activeHandles` field. The code was added for testability in `runReconciliation()`
    but incorrectly used `getSchedulerDeps()` (which returns `SchedulerDeps`) instead of the
    module-level `activeHandles` import. `npx tsc --noEmit` was failing silently (0 errors shown
    because tsc exited 0 but the type error was real).
    Fix: Changed `const handles = deps.activeHandles ?? activeHandles` to
    `const handles = activeHandles` in the Inngest step. The module-level import is correct here.
    Commit: same.

